fields.course_abstract: This demonstration course is not intended to be a usable learning resource. Its sole purpose is to assist in the development of our online learning platform. In the three lessons, we will introduce the Blender 3D package, review some Blender-made artwork, learn the basics of the user interface and of controlling the 3D viewport.
Learn the capital cities of Earth. Fully equip yourself for your next visit (to Earth)

fields.abstract: Be clear what Blender is, where to download it, what it can achieve, sources of community support.
Develop basic familiarity with the main parts of the default user interface.

Learn how to use the number pad to control your point of view in the 3D viewport.
Watch the video that accompanies this lesson, then load the faceviewcube.blend file into blender and try it out for yourself.
Features of the 7 continents of Earth.
Blank lesson to debug next/prev links

fields.att_desc: The blender file for this lesson.

fields.li_text: Recognise a range of tasks for which Blender could be used

fields.criterion_text: Consider where a manual method might have advantages
Try out alternative software and compare with Blender
Talk about the advantages/disadvantages of Blender compared to other approaches

fields.lo_text: I can correctly identify or reject various tasks as being well suited to Blender
I can state whether the main techique of a task involves modelling, sequencing, animating or physics simulation
I can make a selection of appropriate tool or technique for a given job
I can give reasons supporting selection of a particular tool or technique.
